    "x G σðnÞ ðxÞuðr À xÞ, ð31Þ",
    "where G σ(n) is a blurring kernel with varying standard deviation that reduces the high-frequency components of the field with distance, and β(n) is a function that returns a coefficient to dampen the effect of the field with distance.",
    "In our experiments, we used σðnÞ = cn and βðnÞ = maxð1 À n d,0Þ,",
    "with c = 0.2 (measured in pixels) and d = 200 (measured in sections).",
    "The effect of applying a varying blurring kernel on each stitching field was generated by trilinearly interpolating a MIP hierarchy of the field generated using an iterative 2 × 2 box filter 38."
